    dc:creator "Damián-Parizaca, Alexander", "Mitidieri-Rivera, Nicole" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Vanilla cameroniana (Orchidaceae, Vanilloideae), a new species from French Guiana and new records from the Guiana Shield" ;
    bibo:endPage "232" ;
    bibo:issue "3" ;
    bibo:journal "Phytotaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-08-24" ;
    bibo:startPage "222" ;
    bibo:volume "609" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8283232>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8283234>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8283236> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8283232>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Labellum comparison of morphological similar species. A. to V. cameroniana. B. V. hartii. C. V. appendiculata. D–E. V. sprucei. Based on (A) Sabatier D. & Prevost M.-F 4912 (French Guiana, SEL), (B) Stevens 20021 (Nicaragua, SEL), (C) J. Pizango JPF003 (Perú, USM), (D) Redden 1843 (Guyana, US), (E) Redden 2518 (Guyana, US). Photographs by A. Damián (A, B, D, E) and N. Mitidieri (C)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8283232/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8283234>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Geographic distribution of the species discussed in this study, including the limits of the Guiana Shield. The black-colored datapoints on the map represent occurrences documented in the GBIF database, while the blue-colored datapoints indicate new records reported in this study. Additionally, red datapoints represent the newly described species. The asterisk (*) is used to indicate type material." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8283234/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8283236>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. New Vanilla records from the Guiana Shield based on herbarium material. A–F Vanilla sprucei, A–B. perianth dissection, C–D. labellum apex, E–F. column apex and anther. G–H. Vanilla dressleri, I. Vanilla corinnae. Based on Redden 2518, US (A,C,E); Redden 1843, US (B,D,F); Cremers 13016, NY (G); Wurdack 43074, US (H); and Wurdack 43170, US (I). Photographs by A. Damián." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8283236/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

